The solution provided in the [accepted answer](https://stackoverflow.com/a/45595908/10819573) works only if you execute it on a machine with `ENGLISH` as the default `Locale`; it will fail otherwise. 

[Never use `SimpleDateFormat` or `DateTimeFormatter` without a Locale](https://stackoverflow.com/a/65544056/10819573) because they are `Locale`-sensitive. Use the following one to avoid failure due to the default `Locale` not matching the input.

    DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern(&quot;h[:mm]a&quot;, Locale.ENGLISH);

**Demo**:

